: "Water;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, S, M, K;) and so ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bulaAlN", "text_ar": "بُلَالٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "balaAlN", "text_ar": "بَلَالٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (K.) You say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA fiY siqaAy^ihi bilaAlN", "text_ar": "مَا فِى سِقَايِهِ بِلَالٌ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "There is not in his skin any water:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, S:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "anything whatever:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(so in a copy of the S:) and in like manner one"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 245}, {"kind": "text", "text": "says of a well. (T.) And ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA fiY Albiy^ori baAluwlN", "text_ar": "مَا فِى البِيْرِ بَالُولٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "There is not any water in the well."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K.) ―         -b3-  And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Anything with which one moistens the fauces, of water or of milk:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Msb, K:) such is said to be its meaning. (Msb.) ―         -b4-  And hence the saying,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AinoDaHuwA Alr~aHima bibalaAlihaA", "text_ar": "اِنْضَحُوا الرَّحِمَ بِبَلَالِهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", i. e."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SiluwhaA biSilatihaA", "text_ar": "صِلُوهَا بِصِلَتِهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Make ye close the ties of relationship by behaving with that goodness and affection and gentleness to kindred which those ties require:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bal~a raHimahu", "text_ar": "بَلَّ رَحِمَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and see also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "balaAli", "text_ar": "بَلَالِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (S.)"}], "source_refs": ["T", "S", "Msb", "K"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translation